<p>Thanks for pointing this out, fixed what I can find. The change in tense within the same paragraph isn't what I intended to do, sorry about those, hopefully it's better now and less confusing. The change of tense should occur when move on to the next section.</p>
<p>It's true that there isn't that much of the story in it, what I was trying to do is to use the tenses to represent the chaotic passage of time + ties things togther. Hopefully by fixing the grammar the former intention can be carried out. I mean, I won't say there's no plot at all, but yeah, totally valid to say there is not much of a story.</p>
<p>Thanks a lot for the critique :3</p>

