<p>I do admit it is a, um, bold idea, that would be difficult to pull through! ;&gt;</p>
<p>Mmh. Lemme try something&#8230; Let's see&#8230; With the last paragraph, for instance&#8230;</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The clock shall strike zero, and the guard and the gate are no longer there. The King <em>was hanging</em> dead and the Dragon <em>emerges</em> again. The clock shall point to zero, and all <em>ended</em>.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>My changes in italics. You did mix up future and present in the first sentence!!<br />
You still have some logic (the clock shall strike, the clock shall point) and no bold innovation (though I am tempted to write 'all shall ended' ;P)&#8230; but the tenses are mixed up.<br />
I think it's OK, but I will understand if you don't! ;&gt;</p>

