			<div class="content" id="post-content-2431210">
									

<p>I think both this and <a href="/midnight-parade">Midnight Parade</a> suffer from being a merely fragmentary narrative that doesn't really progress beyond exposition. This is maybe the start of a story, but it lacks conflict, climax or resolution. It is more of an atmospheric prose poem, than a short story. Evaluated as a prose poem it isn't bad, and the illustrations are, of course, absolutely excellent. I think that I would rather this were developed more as a narrative, though.</p>
<p>I am also a bit disappointed that the thing that I found most interesting on the first read, the sense of disjointed time, was the result of error.</p>

